auling the Korean ruling system, the book also makes the radical proposition that the purpose of government is to serve the interests of the people. This long-awaited translation opens a new window on early-nineteenth century Korea and makes available to a wide audience a work whose main concerns simultaneously transcend national and cultural boundaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCivil service ethicszKorea. 0aLocal officials and employeeszKoreaxConduct of life. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a1821.  aadministrations.  aasian lit.  aconfucianism.  acriminal justice.  acultural boundaries.  adistrict magistrates.  aearly 19th century.  aeconomics.  aencyclopedia reference.  aenglish translation.  afamine relief.  afamous literature.  aglobal literature.  agovernance.  agovernment and governing.  agovernment.  ahistorical.  akorea.  akorean literature.  akorean military.  akorean ruling system.  anonfiction.  apeoples government.  apolitical.  apremodern literature.  aritual system.  asocial history.  asocial welfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026091740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094770240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947702/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY